    <!-- GROUP DESCRIPTIONS -->
    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Little Disciples (Ages 5–7)</h3>
      <p>
        Young children are introduced to the foundations of faith, love, and prayer through joyful and engaging activities
        such as Bible stories, songs, and crafts. These lessons help them build a personal connection to God and the Church.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Young Servants (Ages 7–11)</h3>
      <p>
        This group takes an active role in church life, participating in junior choir and service. Lessons on faith in action,
        traditions, and good character help them grow in responsibility and spiritual maturity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Youth in Faith (Ages 11–15)</h3>
      <p>
        Older youth are guided to strengthen their personal faith through spiritual discussions, mentorship, and community service.
        They are prepared to become active, committed members and faithful examples within the Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Young Adults (Ages 15+)</h3>
      <p>
        The St. Mary's Young Adults Ministry is a vibrant community dedicated to growing in the Tewahedo faith, building strong
        fellowship, and serving the church through spiritual discussions, social events, community outreach, and educational workshops.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- SPECIALIZED LESSONS -->
    <h2>Specialized Lessons</h2>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Begena Lessons (Ages 13+)</h3>
      <p>
        Learn the ancient spiritual art of the Begena — the Harp of David. This class teaches students to play this sacred instrument,
        used for prayer, meditation, and praising God during fasts and vigils, following the tradition of St. Yared.
      </p>
    </div>

